qbPvcMIB.name: qbPvcMIB
qbPvcMIB.description: This module defines additional objects for the provisioning and management of PVC in Quantum bridge devices.

qbEnetPvcNumber.name: qbEnetPvcNumber
qbEnetPvcNumber.description: The total number of provisioned Ethernet to ATM PVCs.

qbEnePvcLastTimeUpdate.name: qbEnePvcLastTimeUpdate
qbEnePvcLastTimeUpdate.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation, deletion or modification of an entry in the qbAtmPvcTable. If the number of entries has been unchanged since the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object contains a zero value.

qbEnetPvcTable.name: qbEnetPvcTable
qbEnetPvcTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Ethernet configuration table contains connections between Ethernet interfaces (IOT and Ethernet Module) and corresponding VCL/AAL5 that are configured at an ATM interface. An entry in the table may be created, destroyed or modified. This table lists all Ethernet AAL5 PVCs within the System that send/receive packet traffic to/from the ATM cloud.

qbEnetPvcEntry.name: qbEnetPvcEntry
qbEnetPvcEntry.description: An entry in the qbEnetPvcTable. There is one entry in the table per Ethernet interface. The creation of a row in this table causes a corresponding entry in the atmVclTable of the ATM-MIB to be automatically created if an atmVclEntry with qbEnetPvcVpi and qbEnetPvcVci values does not exist. This corresponding entry can be removed only if the qbEnetPvcEntry is removed. The qbEnetPvcIndex of this table is an ifIndex of the IOT or Module Ethernet interface from the ifTable.

qbEnetPvcIndex.name: qbEnetPvcIndex
qbEnetPvcIndex.description: The value of this object is equal to MIB II's ifIndex value of the IOT or 24-Port Enet Port interface.

qbEnetPvcAtmIndex.name: qbEnetPvcAtmIndex
qbEnetPvcAtmIndex.description: The value of this object is equal to MIB II's ifIndex value of the ATM Port interface mapped to an Ethernet interface.

qbEnetPvcVpi.name: qbEnetPvcVpi
qbEnetPvcVpi.description: A VPI of the AAL5 bi-directional PVC that connects this interface to the ATM cloud.

qbEnetPvcVci.name: qbEnetPvcVci
qbEnetPvcVci.description: A VCI of the AAL5 bi-directional PVC that connects this interface to the ATM cloud.

qbEnetPvcName.name: qbEnetPvcName
qbEnetPvcName.description: The textual name of the connection(PVC) as specified by a user. It provides a non-volatile handle for this PVC. The supplied name in the qbAtmPvcName is associated with the same PVC for as long as that PVC/conection remains.

qbEnetPvcRxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbEnetPvcRxTrafficDescrIndex
qbEnetPvcRxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this VCL.

qbEnetPvcTxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbEnetPvcTxTrafficDescrIndex
qbEnetPvcTxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this VCL.

qbEnetPvcAdminStatus.name: qbEnetPvcAdminStatus
qbEnetPvcAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the Ethernet connection The up and down states indicate that the traffic flow is enabled or disabled respectively across the ATM cloud.

qbEnetPvcOperStatus.name: qbEnetPvcOperStatus
qbEnetPvcOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the connect.

qbEnetPvcLastChange.name: qbEnetPvcLastChange
qbEnetPvcLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this PVC entered its current operational state.

qbEnetPvcConnKind.name: qbEnetPvcConnKind
qbEnetPvcConnKind.description: The connection type. Two types of connection can be provisioned on the Enet port (modEnetToAtm and iotEnetToAtm)

qbEnetPvcLoopback.name: qbEnetPvcLoopback
qbEnetPvcLoopback.description: This object enables loopback on the ENET or ATM enedpoint.

qbEnetPvcLoopbackSide.name: qbEnetPvcLoopbackSide
qbEnetPvcLoopbackSide.description: This object enables loopback on the IOT ENET enedpoint.

qbEnetPvcRowStatus.name: qbEnetPvcRowStatus
qbEnetPvcRowStatus.description: The status column for this IOT ENET interface. This OBJECT can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following values may be read: active(1) This object may only be set to createAndGo(4). Setting this object to active(1) when its value is already active(1) is a no-op. Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the agent to attempt to create and commit the row based on the contents of the objects in the row. If all necessary information is present in the row and the values are acceptable to the agent, the agent will change the status to active(1). If any of the necessary objects are not available, the agent will reject the creation request. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove the corresponding entry in this table, and disable data traffic.

qbCrossConnPvcNumber.name: qbCrossConnPvcNumber
qbCrossConnPvcNumber.description: The total number of provisioned Enet to Enet, DS1 to DS1, E1 to E1 PVCs.

qbCrossConnPvcLastTimeUpdate.name: qbCrossConnPvcLastTimeUpdate
qbCrossConnPvcLastTimeUpdate.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation, deletion or modification of an entry in the qbAtmPvcTable. If the number of entries has been unchanged since the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object contains a zero value.

qbCrossConnPvcTable.name: qbCrossConnPvcTable
qbCrossConnPvcTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Pvc cross-connection table. This table defines Enet, DS1, or E1 port point-to-point cross-connections within a single OAS system. The connection can be set between two Ethernet, two DS1 or two E1 ports. The table has two indexes: the interface index of the first end-point and the interface index of the second endpoint. Note: Connections that are listed in this table are not reflected in the atmVclTable.

qbCrossConnPvcEntry.name: qbCrossConnPvcEntry
qbCrossConnPvcEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum Bridge qbCrossConnPvcTable two contains a connection between the same port type of IOTs or Modules(Enet and DS1).

qbCrossConnPvcLowIfIndex.name: qbCrossConnPvcLowIfIndex
qbCrossConnPvcLowIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the first interface(lower index) for the configured PVC cross-connect.

qbCrossConnPvcHighIfIndex.name: qbCrossConnPvcHighIfIndex
qbCrossConnPvcHighIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the second interface(higher index) for the configured PVC cross-connect.

qbCrossConnPvcAdminStatus.name: qbCrossConnPvcAdminStatus
qbCrossConnPvcAdminStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this VCL.

qbCrossConnPvcOperStatus.name: qbCrossConnPvcOperStatus
qbCrossConnPvcOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the connection.

qbCrossConnPvcLastChange.name: qbCrossConnPvcLastChange
qbCrossConnPvcLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this connection entered its current operational state.

qbCrossConnPvcRxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbCrossConnPvcRxTrafficDescrIndex
qbCrossConnPvcRxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this connection.

qbCrossConnPvcTxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbCrossConnPvcTxTrafficDescrIndex
qbCrossConnPvcTxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this connection.

qbCrossConnPvcName.name: qbCrossConnPvcName
qbCrossConnPvcName.description: The textual name of the connection as specified by a user. It provides a non-volatile handle for this connection. The supplied name in the qbIotPortConnName is associated with the same connection for as long as that conection remains.

qbCrossConnPvcConnKind.name: qbCrossConnPvcConnKind
qbCrossConnPvcConnKind.description: The connection type. The following connection types can be provisioned on the Enet port iotDs1ToIotDs11, iotE1ToIotE1, iotEnetToIotEnet, iotEnetToModEnet, modE1ToModE1, modDs1ToModDs1,iotEnetToModEnet, iotE1ToModE1, iotDs1ToModDs1.

qbCrossConnPvcLoopback.name: qbCrossConnPvcLoopback
qbCrossConnPvcLoopback.description: This object enables loopback on this IOT to IOT port enedpoint. The endpoint on which loopback is enabled is defined by qbIotPortCrossConnLoopbackEndpt.

qbCrossConnPvcLoopbackSide.name: qbCrossConnPvcLoopbackSide
qbCrossConnPvcLoopbackSide.description: This object defines loopback on the selected endpoint.

qbCrossConnPvcRowStatus.name: qbCrossConnPvcRowStatus
qbCrossConnPvcRowStatus.description: The status of the port connect entry. Changing the value of this object from 'active' to 'destroy' will remove this entry from the database. It will disrupt traffic between two IOT packet interfaces.

qbPvcConnNum.name: qbPvcConnNum
qbPvcConnNum.description: The total number of provisioned Enet to Enet, DS1 to DS1, E1 to E1 PVCs.

qbPvcConnTableLastTimeUpdate.name: qbPvcConnTableLastTimeUpdate
qbPvcConnTableLastTimeUpdate.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation, deletion or modification of an entry in the qbPvcConnTable. If the number of entries has been unchanged since the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object contains a zero value.

qbPvcNextConnId.name: qbPvcNextConnId
qbPvcNextConnId.description: This object returns the lowest unused connection Id.

qbPvcConnTable.name: qbPvcConnTable
qbPvcConnTable.description: This table contains the generic data pertaining to connections. For R3.0 this is limited to ethernet, VLAN, GigE and IOT Enet cross connects.

qbPvcConnEntry.name: qbPvcConnEntry
qbPvcConnEntry.description: Each row provides data for a single connection.

qbPvcConnId.name: qbPvcConnId
qbPvcConnId.description: This is a unique identifier for this connection.

qbPvcConnAdminStatus.name: qbPvcConnAdminStatus
qbPvcConnAdminStatus.description: This is the connection admin status.

qbPvcConnOperStatus.name: qbPvcConnOperStatus
qbPvcConnOperStatus.description: This is the connection oper status.

qbPvcConnTxTd.name: qbPvcConnTxTd
qbPvcConnTxTd.description: This is the traffic descriptor for traffic going from endpoint 1 to endpoint 2.

qbPvcConnRxTd.name: qbPvcConnRxTd
qbPvcConnRxTd.description: This is the traffic descriptor for traffic going from endpoint 2 to endpoint 1.

qbPvcConnEndpt1.name: qbPvcConnEndpt1
qbPvcConnEndpt1.description: This is connection endpoint 1. The following are examples of using this object: ATM endpoint 200.33.43 (ATM interface index of 200, VPI 33, VCI 43) Ethernet endpoint 5002 (Ifindex of ethernet port) Vlan endpoint 23.2 (vlanindex of 23 and vlan port 2) GigE endpoint 201.25 (GigE ifindex of 201 and vlanid 25)

qbPvcConnEndpt2.name: qbPvcConnEndpt2
qbPvcConnEndpt2.description: This is connection endpoint 2( See examples in qbPvcEndpt1).

qbPvcConnEndpt1Type.name: qbPvcConnEndpt1Type
qbPvcConnEndpt1Type.description: This is the type for endpoint 1.

qbPvcConnEndpt2Type.name: qbPvcConnEndpt2Type
qbPvcConnEndpt2Type.description: This is the type for endpoint 2.

qbPvcConnEndpt1Loop.name: qbPvcConnEndpt1Loop
qbPvcConnEndpt1Loop.description: This controls PVC loopbacks on endpoint 1.

qbPvcConnEndpt2Loop.name: qbPvcConnEndpt2Loop
qbPvcConnEndpt2Loop.description: This controls PVC loopbacks on endpoint 2.

qbPvcConnRowStatus.name: qbPvcConnRowStatus
qbPvcConnRowStatus.description: The row status column for this Vlan. This OBJECT can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following values may be read: active(1) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the agent to attempt to create and commit the row based on the contents of the objects in the row. If all necessary information is present in the row and the values are acceptable to the agent, the agent will change the status to active(1). If any of the necessary objects are not available, the agent will reject the creation request. When a row is created in this table, there will also be 2 corresponding rows created in the table qbPvcMappingTable. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove the corresponding entry in this table, and disable data traffic. When this row is deleted the 2 corresponding rows in the qbPvcMappingTable will also be deleted.

qbPvcConnMappingTable.name: qbPvcConnMappingTable
qbPvcConnMappingTable.description: This table contains the data to map from the first index of the connection endpoint to connection ID.

qbPvcConnMappingEntry.name: qbPvcConnMappingEntry
qbPvcConnMappingEntry.description: Each row maps from an specific endpoint to a specific connection.

qbPvcConnMappingType.name: qbPvcConnMappingType
qbPvcConnMappingType.description: This is the type of endpoint that the next index refers to.

qbPvcConnMappingIndex.name: qbPvcConnMappingIndex
qbPvcConnMappingIndex.description: This is the first index for the connection endpoint. For most connection endpoint this will be the ifIndex, however for VLAN endpoints, this will be the VLAN index.

qbPvcConnMappingId.name: qbPvcConnMappingId
qbPvcConnMappingId.description: This is the connection Id for the connection this entry pertains to.

qbPvcCompliance.name: qbPvcCompliance
qbPvcCompliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

qbEnetPvcGroupInfo.name: qbEnetPvcGroupInfo
qbEnetPvcGroupInfo.description: The set of all accessible objects in the ATM PVC Network Group of this MIB.

qbCrossConnPvcGroupInfo.name: qbCrossConnPvcGroupInfo
qbCrossConnPvcGroupInfo.description: The set of all accessible objects in the Cross-Connect PVC Group of this MIB.
